  "overview": {
    "leader": {
      "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/V%C3%ADctor_Paz_Estenssoro",
      "body": "Victor Paz Estenssoro was the 45th President of Bolivia, serving a total of four terms on three non-consecutive occasions. He was renowned as an effective leader, though one whose political alignment shifted significantly over his life. In the 1950s, he was a leftist reformer who nationalized the mines; in the 1980s, a neoliberal centrist who privatized them again.",
      "title": "Victor Paz Estenssoro"
    },
    "civilization": {
      "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bolivia",
      "body": "Bolivia, officially the Plurinational State of Bolivia, is a landlocked country located in western-central South America. The capital is Sucre while the seat of government is located in La Paz. The largest city and principal economic and financial center is Santa Cruz de la Sierra, located on the Llanos Orientales (tropical lowlands) a mostly flat region in the east of Bolivia.",
      "title": "Bolivia"
    }
  },
  "dawnOfMan": {
    "defeat": "\"I shudder to imagine what this country will become without me.\"",
    "blessing": "\"Salutations, Victor Paz Estenssoro, one of the most tenacious and versatile politicians in Bolivian history! Throughout your four terms as President of Bolivia, you held a wide range of political positions as the country needed. In your early career, you were a staunch left-wing reformist; you nationalized the mines, passed universal suffrage, and redistributed farmland throughout the nation. You would then go on to disarm the militias and restore power to the military, though this would lead to your overthrow. When you returned to power in the 1980s, you had become a centrist, and addressed the economic crisis by re-privatizing the mines and correcting prices. Sober and careful, yet still with a strong sense of vision, you have become one of Bolivia's most memorable presidents in history.\nPresident Paz, the Bolivian people call for you to return to your place at the country's helm. Can you use your famed adaptability to take on every challenge the world might throw at you? Can you build a civilization that will stand the test of time?\"",
    "introduction": "\"Welcome to Bolivia. I am her president, Victor Paz Estenssoro. I hope our nations can maintain agreeable relations.\""
  },
